Recognizing the TCP Connection process

1.Connection oriented transport
2.Begins with a three way handshake
3.Ends by terminating the session

A three way handshake begins by the client sending a SYN packet to the server
That SYN packet synchronizes the sequence numbers,
If the server accepts, it responds by a synchronization acknowledgement
The client then sends a final acknowledgement, a connection is established
A socket is created and we can begin to exchange data

Refusing a Connection

-> SYN packet with a RST
-> No response may mean a firewall
-> ICMP destination unreachable packet
-> The host may try again with another SYN packet


A connection can be terminated in one of several ways

-> The connection will be timed out and will be closed
-> No password sent, so the connection is RST
-> An exchange of FIN packets for normal termination



A normal termination  - 
Client sends an ACK to Server, and Server replied with FIN-ACK to Client
Client sends an FIN-ACK to Server, and Server sends an ACK to Client

